ARGUMENT
w x y z

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_dfcnqs | |- CC = ( ( R. X. R. ) /. `' _E ) |
| 2 |  | #P_mulcnsrec | |- ( ( ( x e. R. /\ y e. R. ) /\ ( z e. R. /\ w e. R. ) ) -> ( [ <. x , y >. ] `' _E x. [ <. z , w >. ] `' _E ) = [ <. ( ( x .R z ) +R ( -1R .R ( y .R w ) ) ) , ( ( y .R z ) +R ( x .R w ) ) >. ] `' _E ) |
| 3 |  | #P_mulcnsrec | |- ( ( ( z e. R. /\ w e. R. ) /\ ( x e. R. /\ y e. R. ) ) -> ( [ <. z , w >. ] `' _E x. [ <. x , y >. ] `' _E ) = [ <. ( ( z .R x ) +R ( -1R .R ( w .R y ) ) ) , ( ( w .R x ) +R ( z .R y ) ) >. ] `' _E ) |
| 4 |  | #P_mulcomsr | |- ( x .R z ) = ( z .R x ) |
| 5 |  | #P_mulcomsr | |- ( y .R w ) = ( w .R y ) |
| 6 | 5 | #P_oveq2i | |- ( -1R .R ( y .R w ) ) = ( -1R .R ( w .R y ) ) |
| 7 | 4, 6 | #P_oveq12i | |- ( ( x .R z ) +R ( -1R .R ( y .R w ) ) ) = ( ( z .R x ) +R ( -1R .R ( w .R y ) ) ) |
| 8 |  | #P_mulcomsr | |- ( y .R z ) = ( z .R y ) |
| 9 |  | #P_mulcomsr | |- ( x .R w ) = ( w .R x ) |
| 10 | 8, 9 | #P_oveq12i | |- ( ( y .R z ) +R ( x .R w ) ) = ( ( z .R y ) +R ( w .R x ) ) |
| 11 |  | #P_addcomsr | |- ( ( z .R y ) +R ( w .R x ) ) = ( ( w .R x ) +R ( z .R y ) ) |
| 12 | 10, 11 | #P_eqtri | |- ( ( y .R z ) +R ( x .R w ) ) = ( ( w .R x ) +R ( z .R y ) ) |
| 13 | 1, 2, 3, 7, 12 | #P_ecovcom | |- ( ( A e. CC /\ B e. CC ) -> ( A x. B ) = ( B x. A ) ) |
\
 Multiplication of complex numbers is commutative.  Axiom 8 of 22 for real and complex numbers, derived from ZF set theory.  This construction-dependent theorem should not be referenced directly, nor should the proven axiom ~ ax-mulcom be used later.  Instead, use ~ mulcom .  (Contributed by NM, 31-Aug-1995.) (New usage is discouraged.)
